Package: cryptkey-fetch-otp
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Richard Oliver <richard.oliver@raspberrypi.com>
Depends: busybox | coreutils, xxd, raspi-utils-core
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Read private key from Raspberry Pi OTP memory
 Reads a private key from the Raspberry Pi OTP (one-time programmable)
 memory via vcmailbox. Used by cryptroot as a fallback key source when
 cryptkey-rpifwcrypto is unavailable. Supports BCM2711 and BCM2712 chips.
 Note: OTP rows are visible to any user in the 'video' group, so this is
 only suitable for key storage when signed boot is enabled.
